  "text": "The Java ClassLoader delegation chain in OpenJDK involves both Java and native C++ components working together:\n\n1. **Java Layer - Parent-First Delegation (src/java.base/share/classes/java/lang/ClassLoader.java)**\n   - The `ClassLoader.loadClass(String name, boolean resolve)` method (line 534) implements the core parent-first delegation strategy. It first checks if the class is already loaded via `findLoadedClass(name)`, then delegates to the parent loader via `parent.loadClass(name, false)`, and only calls `findClass(name)` if the parent fails or returns null.\n\n2. **Built-in Loaders Base Class (src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/BuiltinClassLoader.java)**\n   - `BuiltinClassLoader` extends `ClassLoader` and serves as the base class for the three built-in loaders. It overrides `loadClass(String cn, boolean resolve)` and provides `loadClassOrNull()` which returns null instead of throwing exceptions. It also implements module-aware class loading with methods like `findClass(String cn)` that can load classes from both modules and classpath.\n\n3. **Built-in Loaders Creation (src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/ClassLoaders.java)**\n   - The `ClassLoaders` class creates and manages the three built-in class loaders:\n     - `BootClassLoader` (line 131): Loads classes from the boot module path\n     - `PlatformClassLoader` (line 146): Loads platform modules, delegates to BootClassLoader as parent\n     - `AppClassLoader` (line 161): Loads application classes, delegates to PlatformClassLoader as parent\n   - These loaders are initialized in a static block, establishing the delegation hierarchy: App → Platform → Boot.\n\n4. **HotSpot Native Loading (src/hotspot/share/classfile/classLoader.cpp and classLoader.hpp)**\n   - The C++ `ClassLoader::load_class()` method (line 1141 in .cpp, declared at line 347 in .hpp) handles low-level class file loading from the file system. It searches through the boot classpath including --patch-module entries, jimage modules, and exploded module builds. This method converts class names to file names and retrieves the class file streams.\n\n5. **System Dictionary - Class Caching (src/hotspot/share/classfile/systemDictionary.hpp and systemDictionary.cpp)**\n   - The `SystemDictionary` class maintains a cached dictionary of all loaded classes per `ClassLoaderData`. Key methods include:\n     - `resolve_or_fail()`: Resolves a class name and throws an exception if not found\n     - `resolve_or_null()`: Resolves a class name and returns null if not found\n   - The dictionary uses a concurrent hash table with a fixed number of buckets. During class loading, the class loader object is locked, and the global `SystemDictionary_lock` is held for all additions to class loader data dictionaries. This ensures thread-safe caching of loaded classes and prevents circular loading dependencies through placeholder mechanisms."
}

